\title{\textbf{Axiom AI Lesson Generator}\\
\large Research Integration UI Specification}
\author{Michael Reid}
\date{\today}

\begin{document}

\maketitle

\section{Overview}

This document defines the User Interface (UI) specification for integrating multi-source research capabilities into the Axiom AI Lesson Generator system. The system incorporates:

\begin{itemize}
\item YouTube (visual learning)
\item GitHub (implementation and code examples)
\item Research Papers (academic depth)
\end{itemize}

The goal is to transform the application into a structured academic intelligence platform.

\section{Main Layout}

\subsection{Screen Structure}

\begin{itemize}
\item Header: Topic input and system controls
\item Lesson Workspace: Content editor and YAML preview
\item Research Panel: Multi-source research interface
\item Footer: Agent activity and system status
\end{itemize}

\subsection{Layout Diagram}

\begin{center}
\begin{tikzpicture}[
    box/.style={draw, rectangle, minimum width=5cm, minimum height=1.2cm}
]

\node[box] (header) {Header: Topic Input + Controls};
\node[box, below=0.3cm of header] (main) {Lesson Workspace \hspace{2cm} Research Panel};
\node[box, below=0.3cm of main] (footer) {Agent Status / Build Progress};

\end{tikzpicture}
\end{center}

\section{Research Panel}

\subsection{Structure}

\begin{itemize}
\item Topic Search Input
\item Tabs: YouTube, GitHub, Papers
\item Results Panel (scrollable)
\item Add-to-Lesson functionality
\end{itemize}

\section{YouTube Integration}

\subsection{Purpose}

Provide visual explanations and conceptual reinforcement.

\subsection{Card Components}

\begin{itemize}
\item Thumbnail
\item Title
\item Duration and channel
\item Summary (bullet points)
\item Buttons: Watch, Add to Lesson
\end{itemize}

\subsection{Data Model}

\begin{verbatim}
video_id
title
channel
duration
thumbnail
summary
category
\end{verbatim}

\subsection{Lesson Mapping}

\begin{itemize}
\item Resource Type: video
\item Placement: Concept Visualization
\end{itemize}

\section{GitHub Integration}

\subsection{Purpose}

Provide real-world code examples and implementation references.

\subsection{Repository Card}

\begin{itemize}
\item Repository name
\item Star count
\item Programming language
\item Description
\item Key files
\item Buttons: View Repo, Extract Example
\end{itemize}

\subsection{Code Extraction}

When a user selects a file:

\begin{itemize}
\item Code preview is displayed
\item Cleaned and formatted for lesson integration
\end{itemize}

\subsection{Data Model}

\begin{verbatim}
repo_name
description
stars
language
url
example_files
example_code
\end{verbatim}

\subsection{Lesson Mapping}

\begin{itemize}
\item Resource Type: code example
\item Placement: Worked Example
\end{itemize}

\section{Research Papers Integration}

\subsection{Purpose}

Provide theoretical depth and academic validation.

\subsection{Card Components}

\begin{itemize}
\item Title
\item Authors
\item Year
\item Abstract summary
\item Key contributions
\item Buttons: View Paper, Summarize
\end{itemize}

\subsection{Data Model}

\begin{verbatim}
title
authors
year
abstract
summary
pdf_link
source
\end{verbatim}

\subsection{Lesson Mapping}

\begin{itemize}
\item Resource Type: research reference
\item Placement: Advanced Insight
\end{itemize}

\section{Resource Tagging System}

\subsection{Tags}

\begin{longtable}{ll}
\toprule
Tag & Meaning \\
\midrule
Concept & Core explanation \\
Example & Worked problem \\
Visual & Video or diagram \\
Advanced & Research-level insight \\
\bottomrule
\end{longtable}

\section{Lesson Integration Structure}

\subsection{Generated Lesson Sections}

\begin{itemize}
\item Concept Explanation
\item Visual Resource (YouTube)
\item Worked Example (GitHub Code)
\item Advanced Insight (Research Papers)
\end{itemize}

\section{Agent Activity Interface}

\subsection{Purpose}

Display real-time processing of system agents.

\subsection{Example}

\begin{verbatim}
Research Agent       ✓ complete
Video Analysis       running
Code Extractor       pending
Lesson Generator     pending
\end{verbatim}

\section{Database Schema}

\subsection{Table: research\_resources}

\begin{verbatim}
id
topic
type
title
source
url
summary
tags
created_at
\end{verbatim}

\subsection{Table: lesson\_resources}

\begin{verbatim}
id
lesson_id
resource_id
placement
order_index
\end{verbatim}

\section{System Workflow}

\begin{center}
\begin{tikzpicture}[
node distance=1.5cm,
every node/.style={draw, rectangle, minimum width=3.5cm, minimum height=1cm},
arrow/.style={->, thick}
]

\node (topic) {Topic Input};
\node (research) [below of=topic] {Research Panel};
\node (select) [below of=research] {User Selection};
\node (lesson) [below of=select] {Lesson Generator};
\node (qc) [below of=lesson] {Quality Control};
\node (latex) [below of=qc] {LaTeX Builder};
\node (output) [below of=latex] {PDF + Slides};

\draw[arrow] (topic) -- (research);
\draw[arrow] (research) -- (select);
\draw[arrow] (select) -- (lesson);
\draw[arrow] (lesson) -- (qc);
\draw[arrow] (qc) -- (latex);
\draw[arrow] (latex) -- (output);

\end{tikzpicture}
\end{center}

\section{Development Priority}

\begin{enumerate}
\item Research Panel
\item YouTube Integration
\item GitHub Integration
\item Add-to-Lesson Feature
\item Resource Tagging System
\item Lesson Integration
\item Research Papers (final stage)
\end{enumerate}

\section{Conclusion}

This UI specification defines a transition from simple content generation to a structured academic intelligence system. The integration of multiple knowledge sources ensures:

\begin{itemize}
\item Improved lesson quality
\item Real-world relevance
\item Academic depth
\item Scalable content generation
\end{itemize}

\end{document}
